summary: So on one hand, I am super annoyed with this. I feel like I get stuck at a number and just can’t wait to see the next one,...
body:
1.29.19 - 267.6 (-8)

So on one hand, I am super annoyed with this. I feel like I get stuck at a number and just can’t wait to see the next one, mostly because I am just so sick of seeing the same one. Lol. 😂 And the crazy thing is my average weight is now 265.9. It keeps going down. I don’t know how to feel about that 🤷‍♀️


On the other hand, NSV, I not only made it to day #2 at the gym, but I crushed my goal of doing 30 minutes on the bike. I was happy about it because yesterday I was only able to do 15 (barely) before my ankle got sore. I switched the type of bike, not sure if that had anything to do with it. But, either way 🙌🏻


I am excited for Weigh In tomorrow to see where I am at after taking the Thermofight X for a week. Hopefully whatever bloating I have going on has subsided by then so I can get an accurate number 🙄 I don’t know what it is. I feel less bloated than yesterday, so that’s a start anyway. I’m going to keep it as clean as possible today so I can sort it out. And maybe avoid dairy. That usually a culprit of bloat. But, ya know, cheese 🧀 🤷‍♀️


Welp, that’s my update for today. I hope you all have a splendid Tuesday! 💓

summary: Hi Jennie, how do I feel better about missing a day of work? I was sick, and I couldn't go to work and now I just feel very...
question: Hi Jennie, how do I feel better about missing a day of work? I was sick, and I couldn't go to work and now I just feel very guilty/troubled. One, I lose a day's worth of salary, and two, kore importantly I feel that my coworkers would still have come in spite of their illness, of they were in my position. On one hand, I know my body and health comes first, but on the other, it's kind of the "norm" to just power through to show that you're strong. Any advice? Thank you Jennie! Merry Christmas! ❤️
answer:
I really dislike the workplace culture that pressures people to ‘power through’ at the expense of their (and other people’s) health. Were you going to be able to do your work to the best of your ability while you were sick? Probably not. Would you be putting your coworkers, customers or clients at risk of catching your illness if you went to work? Probably. Personally, I think you 100% made the right decision not to go to work if you felt like you couldn’t go to work. Just because some of your coworkers might have gone to work anyway doesn’t mean that it’s the right thing to do.

(Couple of things to remember about the ‘norm’ of powering through: a) many people go into work when they’re sick, not because they want to, but because they literally can’t afford to lose a day’s pay, and b) the rules and regulations regarding sick pay and how many days off a worker can take are all made up by billionaires who can take as many sick days as they want.)

There’s not really anything you can do about it now, and you might still feel troubled by it, but try to remember that there is nothing wrong with taking care of your health.

body:
Monday, January 28th, 2019

Stress Management Techniques

tea time ❌

aromatherapy ❌

deep breathing/meditation ❌

stick to fucking bedtime (you God damn fool) ✔️

neck and shoulder stretches ❌

Habits

stop picking at face ❌

limit of two caffeinated beverages (one is green tea) ✔️

go back to sleep after my inevitable bathroom break ✔️

journal ✔️

tidy up at least one thing/place in the house ✔️

no dairy ❌

lightbox ❌

IT IS ALL SHOWING

Medication Taken

Zoloft, Topamax (AM+PM), Probiotic, Vitamin D, Iron/B12/Folate, Calcium, Melatonin ✔️

Goals

At least 30 minutes of Spanish ❌

Dedicated Workouts (0/4)

I mean, I really can’t work out for now…so.

It just wouldn’t be my personal sheet music if there weren’t food and coffee stains on it. It was a beautiful snow day on Monday so I sort of just played around on the piano to see if I wanted to edit this piece at all. Though, of course, I have to drive around in that snow now. Not looking forward to that. I mean, thank God for AWD but, barf.

So, I actually arsed myself to make my horrific spinach applesauce and very steamed green beans and as much I poo poo’d it, it was my favorite thing I ate yesterday. I mean, I pretty much like eating salads with so much ruffage I wouldn’t notice if there were sticks in it, but this is what I have to do for now. It was just so nice to eat ANYTHING green.

I had a decent amount of energy for most of the day, but by sundown, I was run over and my joints really started to ache. Uh? Too young for this shit. Itched everywhere. OMG. I’ll shut up now.

Migraine Zone

Not gonna lie. I’m sorta dreading Tuesday. If pattern serves right, I might have a monster of a migraine start sometime tomorrow. The last two periods I’ve had have been God awful. I’ve pre-emptively been wearing my Axons just hoping any reduction in environmental stressors helps out. We’ll seeeeeeeeee? It’s not gonna help that I can’t really risk eating much; if anything, before I’m done with my errands. Lord, save me.
